---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Yarn Yardage Calculator" description="Learn how this free yarn yardage calculator works, where the data comes from, and why it exists." canonical="https://yarn-yardage-calculator.vercel.app/about">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">

    <!-- Breadcrumb JSON-LD -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://yarn-yardage-calculator.vercel.app/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://yarn-yardage-calculator.vercel.app/about" }
      ]
    })} />

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-6">About This Calculator</h1>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none space-y-6 text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
      <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-3">What It Does</h2>
        <p>The Yarn Yardage Calculator estimates how much yarn you need for knitting and crochet projects. It's designed for crafters who want a quick, reliable estimate before buying yarn for scarves, blankets, sweaters, hats, socks, shawls, or any custom project.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-3">How It Works</h2>
        <p>The calculator uses the Craft Yarn Council's Standard Yarn Weight System as its foundation. For each yarn weight (Lace through Jumbo), we use:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mt-3">
          <li>Typical gauge ranges for knitting</li>
          <li>Empirical yardage-per-stitch factors derived from common yarn usage</li>
          <li>Standard skein sizes per weight category</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">You provide your project dimensions and actual gauge (or use our auto-fill), and the calculator estimates total yardage, meters, and skeins needed — with a 15% safety buffer.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-3">Data Sources</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Craft Yarn Council</strong> — Standard Yarn Weight System (yarn weights, gauge ranges, needle/hook sizes)</li>
          <li><strong>Empirical yarn factors</strong> — Derived from analysis of thousands of Ravelry projects and yarn specifications</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-3">Why Another Yarn Calculator?</h2>
        <p>Existing yarn tools focus on weight combining (mixing strands) or database lookups. We built this because there wasn't a simple, focused tool that answers the most common question: <em>"How much yarn do I need for my project?"</em> — no account, no pattern browsing, just quick estimates.</p>
      </section>

      <section class="bg-[var(--color-bg-card)] rounded-xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border)]">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)] mb-3">Disclaimer</h2>
        <p class="text-sm">This calculator provides estimates only. Actual yarn requirements vary based on tension, stitch pattern, yarn properties, and individual technique. Always buy extra yarn (10-20%) and make a gauge swatch before starting your project. Not affiliated with Craft Yarn Council.</p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
